text: Firuzabad County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Firuzabad.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 111,973, in 24,894 families. The county is subdivided into two districts: the Central District and Meymand District. The county has two cities: Firuzabad and Meymand. == References == == Other websites == Category:Counties in Fars Province
